description:
&lt;p&gt;Judy Beard Day Unit is looking for dynamic band 5 staff nurses with an interest in haematology /oncology nursing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have one post working 37.5 hours per week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a busy but friendly team delivering a variety of intravenous treatments including chemotherapy, immunotherapy and supportive treatments. You will after training, need to be able to prioritise care, deliver treatments and maintain high standards of nursing care whilst responding sensitively to the needs of this client group.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Good communication skills and the ability to work with the wider MDT are essential. Ideally you will have some experience in venepuncture, cannulation, central lines and IV therapy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At least 2 years post registration experience would be desirable and experience in administration of Chemotherapy is desirable but not essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Whilst on the unit you will have the opportunity to assist the staff with supplementary medical infusions and monoclonal antibody therapy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This will be a great opportunity for an experienced staff nurse to gain valuable experience in this chosen speciality&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hayley Bird&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Matron&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;hayley.bird@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;0300 1314500 Ext 773110 / 771930&lt;/p&gt;
